<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-11-06T09:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-11-06T09:34:00-05:00" n="302" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d302">
                        <head>[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Colon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-11-06T09:15:00-05:19"><hi rend="italic">November 6,
                                        1903, 9.15 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of the Navy</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington, D. C.:</hi></p>
                        <p>Arrived Thursday evening; landed force. Following conditions prevailing:
                            Just before landing all the troops of Colombia have left for R. M. S. P.
                            Company’s steamer <hi rend="italic">Orinoco</hi> for Cartagena.
                            Independent party in possession of Colon, Panama, and railroad line. <hi rend="italic">Nashville</hi> withdrawn force.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Delano.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
